{"lemma":"ضَأْنُ","slug":"ضَأْنُ","root":"ض.#.ن","root_slug":"ض-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضَأْن","root":"ضأن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25416","n25417"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%A3%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sheep","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṣ́aʾn- (“small cattle, sheep”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒇇𒇻𒄭𒀀 (ṣēnum) and Biblical Hebrew צֹאן (ṣoʾn)."},"ipa":["/dˤaʔn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25416","headword_ar":"ضَاْنٌ","root":"DA^n","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA^anN","text_ar":"ضَاَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Day^iynN","text_ar":"ضَيِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) which is also pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Diy^iynN","text_ar":"ضِيِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the first letter because of the kesr following, agreeably with a general rule applying to a word [of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] having any faucial letter [for its second radical], and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiynN","text_ar":"ضِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DayonN","text_ar":"ضَيْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are mentioned by IAar, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore extr., (M,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sheep;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as have wool, of what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganam","text_ar":"غَنَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; one of which is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAy^inN","text_ar":"ضَايِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) [i. e.] they are pls., (S, K,) or [rather] quasi-pl. ns., (M,) of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAy^inN","text_ar":"ضَايِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that has wool,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposite of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAEizN","text_ar":"مَاعِزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganam","text_ar":"غَنَم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA^onN","text_ar":"ضَاْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the fem. gender; (IAmb, Msb;) and has for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDow^unN","text_ar":"اَضْوُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly a pl. of pauc.] (IAmb, M, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=DunN","text_ar":"ا=ضُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which occurs in poetry, and is formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDow^unN","text_ar":"اَضْوُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) the fem. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAy^inN","text_ar":"ضَايِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAy^inapN","text_ar":"ضَايِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb, K;) the pl. of which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaAy^inu","text_ar":"ضَوَايِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA^onN","text_ar":"ضَاْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain species of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lizards called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DibaAb","text_ar":"ضِبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~N","text_ar":"ضَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; opposed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAEiz","text_ar":"مَاعِز"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain species of jerboas, also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufaAriY~N","text_ar":"شُفَارِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadomuriY~N","text_ar":"تَدْمُرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.; and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$fr","text_ar":"شفر"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"differing from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAEiz","text_ar":"مَاعِز"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (T and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dmr","text_ar":"دمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","IAmb"]},{"entry_id":"n25417","headword_ar":"ضَاَنٌ","root":"DA^n","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}